Color of freshly collected male holotype , OMNH-P 35615 : (
Fig. 1
) Body semitranslucent with an internal black stripe centrally along the backbone, extending from opercle posteriorly to caudal-fin base, widest at opercle and tapering posteriorly. Scales on dorsum above black stripe with orange pigment along scale pockets. Scales ventral to those on dorsum with strong black pigment on scale pockets. Ventral half of body silver along abdomen and with seven black internal bars extending from backbone down to ventral midline between anal-fin origin and caudal-fin base. Head red overlaid with many small, black dots as an extension of the black stripe. Nape abruptly orange above red of head and black stripe. Ventral side of head red-orange extending posteriorly to pelvic-fin origin. Genital papilla orange. Pupil of eye surrounded by yellow-gold iris edged in black. First dorsal fin with many small, black dots along basal half. Second dorsal, anal, and caudal fins peppered with many small, black dots. Pelvic-fin rays dusky, membranes clear.

Color of freshly collected female paratype , OMNH-P 35614 : (
Fig. 2
) Body semitranslucent with an internal black stripe centrally along and below the backbone, extending from behind the eye to caudal-fin base. Seven internal black bars extending from backbone down to ventral midline between anal-fin origin and caudal-fin base, with yellow-gold areas between the five posterior black spots. A few short, red triangles extending dorsally from black stripe opposite the black caudal-peduncle spots. Area under first dorsal fin clear, with scale pockets outlined in red. Nape yellow-gold with some red areas. Snout and ventral surface of head red-orange. Ventral surface of head from preopercle back to anal-fin origin silver-white. Pelvic-fin rays dusky, membranes clear. First dorsal fin with reddish spines and many small, black dots along basal half. Second dorsal, anal and caudal fins peppered with many small, black dots, the rays reddish. Eye black.

Color of freshly collected immature paratype , OMNH-P 35254 : (
Fig. 3
) Body translucent from back of head to caudal-fin base. A narrow red stripe above backbone and a broader black stripe below backbone. A series of yellow blotches on upper half of body between backbone and second dorsal-fin base. A few yellow blotches between black stripe and ventral midline on caudal peduncle. A curved orange line above abdomen through the black stripe. Head and nape orange with scattered red and black dots. Ventral surface of head white as is belly and pelvic fins. All other fins with orange membranes. Pupil of eye surrounded by yellowgold iris edged in black.

Color in life: (
Fig. 4
) Body translucent and clear with an internal black stripe centrally along the backbone, extending from the eye posteriorly to the caudal-fin base. The black stripe is widest from the head to the end of the abdomen and then abruptly narrows and tapers to the caudal-fin base. The black stripe with a narrow, bright yellow-gold line that curves down from the dorsal part of the eye to the posterior end of the abdomen. The ventral portion of the black stripe lined with silver along the abdomen and the dorsal portion with a very narrow yellow-gold line that extends from between the eyes to the end of the abdomen. Scale pockets with redish edges dorsally and black edges ventrally. Snout and area behind eye onto cheek red. Lower part of head translucent. Pupil of eye surrounded by a yellow-gold iris with red areas and black on dorsal edge. Peppering of small, black dots on dorsal, anal, and caudal-fin membranes.

Color of holotype in preservative: (
Fig. 5
) Body white with strong black pigment on scale pockets on ventral half of sides of body. Scales on dorsal half white as is the nape. Head overlaid with many small, black dots. A short internal black line at midline of caudal-fin base. Pupil of eye surrounded by white iris, ringed in black. Basal half of first dorsal fin peppered with small, black dots. Second dorsal, anal, and caudal fins peppered with small, black dots.
